    "Out of the three data sources, the PadChest dataset makes up the majority of the dataset, followed by the BIMCV-COVID19 and OpenI datasets (Table 1).",
    "As we did not participate in the multi-modal version of the task, we did not use the radiology images in our experiments.",
    "We experimented with fine-tuning Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct and Qwen3-4B using QLoRA, which injects trainable low-rank adapter layers (LoRA) into specified model layers.",
    "We injected these layers into all the model's linear projection layers, as that tended to result in performance comparable to a fully fine-tuned model according to Dettmers et al. (2023).",
    "We performed our experiments on an NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3090 graphics processing unit (GPU)."
